comments: Professor Davis is an exemplary professor. She is sweet, caring and considerate. She is understanding and respectful to students. Her lectures are interesting and very clear. Loved her class!
I am not recommend her! You should write essays only as she requires. Difficult to get even "B".
I dont think I learned much in her class and I realized that when I went for college writing II. She is not really scrict but not really clear also.

This professor thinks she\'s it. She is very disrespectful to her students. She will not give you the time of day outside of class to raise any issues or concerns. She is very knowledgeable in the field, but is a very poor teacher. In fact, she comes ill prepared, and expects the students to do all the work. I believe she should be fired.
Davis, she thinks she\'s the queen of everything. i would 100% not recommend this class to anyone there are a lot of other teachers out there. trust me!

professors Edna Davis she knows how to teach, but the thing with her is that if you don\'t do her essays the way she wants it to be then you will fail and get a low grade. My best advice is not to take this class what so ever.

Professor Davis really tries to teach how to write. The one thing I disliked is that she has HER style and anyone who has a style which differs from hers will get a low grade. Her classes are interesting and she actually TEACHES. She comes on time and is a fair grader. Very good Professor.
